  "body": "### Version of Hardhat\n\n2.17.4\n\n### What happened?\n\ncannot use viem.deployContract with custom network that is not registered on viem/chains\n\n### Minimal reproduction steps\n\n1. add custom chain\r\n```\r\nchainId: 26657,\r\nurl: \"http://0.0.0.0:8545\",\r\n```\r\n2. run anvil with it\r\n```\r\nanvil --chain-id 26657 --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8545\r\n```\r\n3. run sample script with custom anvil network\r\n```\r\nimport { formatEther, parseEther } from \"viem\";\r\nimport hre from \"hardhat\";\r\n\r\nasync function main() {\r\n  const currentTimestampInSeconds = Math.round(Date.now() / 1000);\r\n  const unlockTime = BigInt(currentTimestampInSeconds + 60);\r\n\r\n  const lockedAmount = parseEther(\"0.001\");\r\n\r\n  const lock = await hre.viem.deployContract(\"Lock\", [unlockTime], {\r\n    value: lockedAmount,\r\n  });\r\n\r\n  console.log(\r\n    `Lock with ${formatEther(\r\n      lockedAmount\r\n    )}ETH and unlock timestamp ${unlockTime} deployed to ${lock.address}`\r\n  );\r\n}\r\n\r\n// We recommend this pattern to be able to use async/await everywhere\r\n// and properly handle errors.\r\nmain().catch((error) => {\r\n  console.error(error);\r\n  process.exitCode = 1;\r\n});\r\n```\r\n\n\n### Search terms\n\nviem",
